West Kelowna Warriors fans are not taking the news the team will be leaving the city at the end of the season lightly. 
The owner of the team, Mark Cheyne said he is in negotiations to sell the team and move it to North Delta. 
READ MORE: West Kelowna Warriors might be on the move 
Cheyne said the team is losing money in West Kelowna. 
A rally has been planned in support of the Junior A hockey team for 5:30 p.m. on Tuesday, Feb. 28 at Royal LePage Place.
